4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill makes supplemental appropriations for
6 the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026 from the
7 Education Trust Fund to various agencies and entities
8 in a total amount of $419,717,091.
9 The bill would also transfer $49,920 from the
10 Alabama Student Assistance Program Fund to the
11 Commission on Higher Education Fund; transfer $148,192
12 from the Knight Court Monitor Fund to the Commission on
13 Higher Education Fund; transfer $114,723 from the
14 Teacher Education Scholarship Loan Fund to the
15 Commission on Higher Education Fund; and make a
16 supplemental appropriation for the fiscal year ending
17 September 30, 2026, from the Commission on Higher
18 Education Fund to the Commission on Higher Education in
19 the amount of $312,835.
20 The bill would make a supplemental appropriation
21 from the CHOOSE Act Fund to the Department of Revenue
22 for the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026 in the
23 amount of $100,000,000.
24 The bill would authorize the Alabama Historical
25 Commission to use returned or unused funds previously
26 appropriated from the Education Trust Fund for
27 historical grants to provide additional grants.
28 This bill would authorize grant funds allocated
Page 1

This bill would authorize grant funds allocated
